			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You're missing a few points:<br />1. If the new point brighter than the old one - the new one is drawn just as they are.<br />2. If the new point darker than the old one - then the strength of the effect will depend on the difference in brightness of the old and the new point. Therefore, the maximum effect will be viewed as a new point - black.<br />3. Each one has a different color phosphor decay rate. I have already given a <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lRidfW_l4vs" class="postlink">link to a video</a> showing it. First fades blue phosphor, then green and red kept the longest. Therefore, it is necessary to work on the sub-pixels separately.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
